# Snapshot: code/stack_intrinsics

## Case 01

### Source: `test/tmp_fs/code.frog`

```frog
1 2 ? print print
```

### Run

Command:

```text
py -m frog run test/tmp_fs/code.frog
```

Output:

```text
[INFO] test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:5: Stack at compile time:
[NOTE] stack:
      0. INT()@test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:1
      1. INT()@test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:3
[INFO] test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:5: Stack at runtime:
[NOTE] stack:
      0. INT():1@test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:1
      1. INT():2@test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:3
[PRINT] INT():2@test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:3
[PRINT] INT():1@test/tmp_fs/code.frog:1:1
```

### Build

Command:

```text
py -m frog -l WARN build -r test/tmp_fs/code.frog
```

Output:

```text
[CMD] gcc test/tmp_fs/code.c -o test/tmp_fs/code.exe
[CMD] test/tmp_fs/code.exe
[STDOUT]:
2
1

```

